org.agilewiki.jactor2.common.transmutable

Interface Transmutable<DATATYPE>

  • Type Parameters:
    DATATYPE - The type of the unmodifiable form--typically an interface.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DurableBox, DurableInt, DurableString, Widget
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BoxFactory.BoxImpl._Box, IntFactory.IntImpl._Int, StringFactory.StringImpl._String, TransmutableArrayList, TransmutableByteBuffer, TransmutableMap, TransmutableSet, TransmutableSortedMap, TransmutableSortedSet, TransmutableString, TSSMap, WidgetFactory.WidgetImpl._Widget

    public interface Transmutable<DATATYPE>
    An object which supports an unmodifiable (read-only) form. The unmodifiable form can be used with complete thread-safety for queries, while the creation of the unmodifiable form typically is not thread safe.
